695
00:58:54.404 --> 00:58:57.448
<i>I will have nothing further to do
with Germans.</i>


696
00:59:04.914 --> 00:59:06.499
<i>April 1945.</i>

697
00:59:08.209 --> 00:59:11.838
<i>The Soviet Army launches
its final assault on Hitler's forces,</i>


698
00:59:11.921 --> 00:59:16.175
<i>encircling Berlin
and closing in on the Führer's bunker.</i>


699
00:59:23.433 --> 00:59:26.644
<i>Hopelessly defeated,
Hitler takes his own life</i>


700
00:59:26.728 --> 00:59:28.730
<i>with a single gunshot to the head.</i>

701
00:59:35.903 --> 00:59:37.822
<i>The war in Europe is won,</i>

702
00:59:37.905 --> 00:59:41.492
<i>but US-led forces continue
their search for a decisive end</i>


703
00:59:41.576 --> 00:59:43.077
<i>to the war with Japan.</i>

704
00:59:44.162 --> 00:59:48.499
<i>Five, four, three, two, one.</i>

705
00:59:50.543 --> 00:59:52.795
<i>After years of scientific endeavor,</i>

706
00:59:52.879 --> 00:59:56.174
<i>the Manhattan Project
has delivered an atomic bomb.</i>


707
01:00:04.015 --> 01:00:06.309
<i>Alamogordo in the New Mexico desert.</i>

708
01:00:06.392 --> 01:00:07.810
<i>The first atomic test.</i>

709
01:00:08.770 --> 01:00:11.522
<i>It's a terrifying prelude
to the onslaught that awaits</i>


710
01:00:11.606 --> 01:00:14.567
<i>the unsuspecting citizens of Hiroshima.</i>

711
01:00:18.321 --> 01:00:20.531
<i>Height approximately 32,000 feet.</i>

712
01:00:21.032 --> 01:00:25.662
<i>Course, 265 degrees magnetic.
Air speed, 250 knots.</i>


713
01:00:27.205 --> 01:00:29.040
<i>Am approaching target area.</i>

714
01:00:29.123 --> 01:00:32.043
<i>Cloud cover less than three-tens
at all altitudes.</i>


715
01:00:32.543 --> 01:00:34.212
<i>Immediate target area clear.</i>

716
01:01:19.257 --> 01:01:20.550
<i>A short time ago,</i>

717
01:01:20.633 --> 01:01:25.346
an American airplane
dropped one bomb on Hiroshima.


718
01:01:27.557 --> 01:01:31.018
<i>What has been done
is the greatest achievement</i>


719
01:01:31.102 --> 01:01:33.646
<i>of organized science in history.</i>

720
01:02:02.008 --> 01:02:06.095
<i>The first atomic bomb heralded
the dawn of a troubling new era.</i>


721
01:02:07.096 --> 01:02:08.222
<i>In a single stroke,</i>

722
01:02:08.306 --> 01:02:12.977
<i>the Japanese city of Hiroshima
and some 70,000 men, women, and children</i>


723
01:02:13.060 --> 01:02:14.061
<i>were annihilated.</i>

724
01:02:15.688 --> 01:02:16.564
<i>In the years since,</i>

725
01:02:16.647 --> 01:02:19.942
<i>that momentous event
has come under increasing scrutiny.</i>


726
01:02:21.611 --> 01:02:24.864
<i>Was the bomb a price
worth paying for peace?</i>


727
01:02:43.800 --> 01:02:45.092
My dear Professor.

728
01:02:49.764 --> 01:02:53.601
At present,
the Japanese people are keenly conscious


729
01:02:53.684 --> 01:02:56.312
of their own responsibility
for the last war.


730
01:02:56.854 --> 01:03:00.942
And are showing
sincere repentance for their crime.


731
01:03:16.582 --> 01:03:20.044
Recently, years since
the termination of the war,


732
01:03:20.795 --> 01:03:23.840
the Japanese people
have come for the first time


733
01:03:23.923 --> 01:03:26.676
face-to-face with the annihilating effects

734
01:03:27.218 --> 01:03:28.302
of an atomic bomb.

735
01:03:31.764 --> 01:03:34.308
And now, we ask you, 
Professor Einstein,

736
01:03:35.059 --> 01:03:36.143
why science,

737
01:03:36.227 --> 01:03:40.147
whose primary aim is but to serve
the welfare and happiness of mankind,


738
01:03:40.648 --> 01:03:44.694
should have been instrumental
in producing such horrible results?


739
01:03:46.237 --> 01:03:51.033
I do not consider myself the father
of the release of atomic energy.


740
01:03:51.117 --> 01:03:53.327
My part in it was quite indirect.

741
01:03:53.411 --> 01:03:56.789
In view of the fact
that <i>you</i> played an important role


742
01:03:56.873 --> 01:03:58.958
in the production of the atomic bombs?

743
01:03:59.041 --> 01:04:02.587
My sole contribution was that in 1905,

744
01:04:02.670 --> 01:04:06.924
I established the relationship
between mass and energy.


745
01:04:09.385 --> 01:04:14.265
I believed only that atomic energy
was theoretically possible.


746
01:04:16.517 --> 01:04:20.980
I did not, in fact,
foresee that atomic energy


747
01:04:21.063 --> 01:04:22.982
would be released in my time.

748
01:04:46.464 --> 01:04:51.135
I made one great mistake in my life.

749
01:04:54.221 --> 01:04:56.766
When I signed that letter
to President Roosevelt.


750
01:05:04.732 --> 01:05:08.653
The likelihood that the Germans
were working on the same problem


751
01:05:08.736 --> 01:05:14.116
with every prospect of success
forced me to take this step.


752
01:06:14.260 --> 01:06:17.471
<i>Had I known
that the Germans would not succeed</i>


753
01:06:17.555 --> 01:06:20.016
<i>in producing an atomic bomb,</i>

754
01:06:21.308 --> 01:06:25.855
<i>I would not have taken part
in opening that Pandora's box.</i>


755
01:06:31.610 --> 01:06:33.863
I never would have lifted a finger.

756
01:06:47.752 --> 01:06:50.129
<i>Before the raid on Hiroshima,</i>

757
01:06:50.212 --> 01:06:53.507
<i>leading physicists
urged the War Department</i>


758
01:06:53.591 --> 01:06:58.137
<i>not to use the bomb
against defenseless women and children.</i>


759
01:07:02.099 --> 01:07:06.312
<i>Had we shown other nations
the test explosion of New Mexico,</i>


760
01:07:07.063 --> 01:07:10.941
<i>we could have used it
to make proposals for world order.</i>


761
01:07:11.025 --> 01:07:12.318
<i>To</i> end <i>war.</i>

762
01:07:16.280 --> 01:07:19.075
<i>The physicists who participated in forging</i>

763
01:07:19.658 --> 01:07:23.829
<i>the most formidable
and dangerous weapon of all time</i>


764
01:07:23.913 --> 01:07:27.792
<i>are harassed
by an equal feeling of responsibility,</i>


765
01:07:28.375 --> 01:07:29.835
<i>not to say guilt.</i>

766
01:07:33.214 --> 01:07:37.760
<i>We delivered this weapon into the hands
of the Americans and the British people</i>


767
01:07:38.427 --> 01:07:41.597
<i>as trustees of the whole mankind,</i>

768
01:07:41.680 --> 01:07:44.225
<i>as fighters for peace and liberty.</i>

769
01:07:46.310 --> 01:07:47.686
<i>But so far,</i>

770
01:07:47.770 --> 01:07:50.648
<i>we fail to see any guarantee of peace</i>

771
01:07:52.191 --> 01:07:55.444
<i>or the freedoms
that were promised to the nations.</i>


772
01:08:04.411 --> 01:08:08.040
The situation calls
for a courageous effort.


773
01:08:09.625 --> 01:08:14.839
For a radical change in our whole attitude

774
01:08:14.922 --> 01:08:18.259
in the entire political concept.

775
01:08:20.886 --> 01:08:21.886
Otherwise,

776
01:08:23.013 --> 01:08:25.266
human civilization will be doomed.

777
01:08:27.143 --> 01:08:28.227
The war is won.

778
01:08:29.645 --> 01:08:30.729
The peace is not.

779
01:08:38.737 --> 01:08:40.632
<i>President Truman's dramatic announcement</i>

780
01:08:40.656 --> 01:08:43.159
<i>that Russia has created
an atomic explosion</i>


781
01:08:43.242 --> 01:08:45.494
<i>sends reporters racing
for Flushing Meadow,</i>


782
01:08:45.578 --> 01:08:48.539
<i>where Russia's Vyshinsky
arrives to address the United Nations.</i>


783
01:08:48.622 --> 01:08:50.541
Mr. Vyshinsky, have you got any statement...

784
01:08:50.624 --> 01:08:54.170
- Please, excuse me.
- Does Russia have the atomic bomb?


785
01:08:57.965 --> 01:09:00.634
<i>A crack, a blast.</i>

786
01:09:00.718 --> 01:09:03.470
<i>The release of deadly radioactive rain.</i>

787
01:09:03.554 --> 01:09:07.975
<i>And in a matter of seconds,
downtown New York would be a massive ruin.</i>


788
01:09:12.354 --> 01:09:13.939
Our country is at war.

789
01:09:14.023 --> 01:09:18.068
A war declared against us
by the rulers of international communism.


790
01:09:18.652 --> 01:09:20.738
<i>This constitutes
the greatest crisis</i>


791
01:09:20.821 --> 01:09:22.489
<i>in the history of America.</i>

792
01:09:22.573 --> 01:09:26.744
<i>There are signs
that the Kremlin is already intensifying</i>


793
01:09:26.827 --> 01:09:28.621
<i>its use of another weapon.</i>

794
01:09:29.121 --> 01:09:30.664
<i>Communist propaganda.</i>

795
01:09:31.624 --> 01:09:35.669
<i>We are in the midst
of a continuing struggle</i>


796
01:09:35.753 --> 01:09:37.546
<i>for the minds of men.</i>

797
01:09:41.592 --> 01:09:44.553
The German calamity
of years ago repeats itself.


798
01:09:46.680 --> 01:09:48.849
People act fierce without resistance

799
01:09:49.600 --> 01:09:52.811
and align themselves
with the forces of evil.


800
01:09:54.688 --> 01:09:57.483
How long should we tolerate politicians

801
01:09:58.317 --> 01:10:03.489
hungry for power or trying to gain
political advantage in such a way?


802
01:10:06.951 --> 01:10:10.996
<i>It is strange that science,
which in the old days seemed harmless,</i>


803
01:10:11.080 --> 01:10:14.917
<i>should have evolved into a nightmare
that causes everyone to tremble.</i>


804
01:10:20.005 --> 01:10:22.883
<i>One thing I have
learned in a long life</i>

805
01:10:22.967 --> 01:10:27.638
<i>is that all our science
measured against reality is childlike.</i>


806
01:10:31.392 --> 01:10:35.145
<i>And yet,
it is the most precious thing we have.</i>


807
01:10:46.282 --> 01:10:50.369
<i>Science is not,
and never will be, a closed book.</i>


808
01:10:52.371 --> 01:10:56.000
<i>Every important advance
brings new questions.</i>


809
01:10:57.793 --> 01:11:01.046
<i>But the years
of anxious searching in the dark</i>


810
01:11:01.130 --> 01:11:03.882
<i>and the final emergence into the light,</i>

811
01:11:05.301 --> 01:11:09.471
<i>only those who have experienced it
can understand.</i>


812
01:11:11.932 --> 01:11:14.059
<i>We must not condemn man</i>

813
01:11:14.143 --> 01:11:16.895
<i>because his conquest
of the forces of nature</i>


814
01:11:16.979 --> 01:11:19.898
<i>are being exploited
for destructive purposes.</i>


815
01:11:20.816 --> 01:11:23.152
<i>Rather, the fate of mankind</i>

816
01:11:23.861 --> 01:11:28.282
<i>hinges entirely upon
man's moral development.</i>


817
01:12:34.807 --> 01:12:36.517
<i>Dear posterity,</i>

818
01:12:37.726 --> 01:12:40.229
<i>if you have not become more just</i>

819
01:12:41.438 --> 01:12:44.775
<i>or peaceful and generally more rational</i>

820
01:12:44.858 --> 01:12:46.652
<i>than we are or were,</i>

821
01:12:47.653 --> 01:12:49.780
<i>then may the devil take you.</i>

822
01:12:51.198 --> 01:12:54.034
<i>I am, or was,</i>

823
01:12:55.327 --> 01:12:57.913
<i>your Albert Einstein.</i>